Step 1 — Define the real costs (this is the missing piece in most projects)

AML is not a prediction problem.
It is a risk economics problem.

You must assign operational costs.

Example realistic cost model:

Event	Meaning	Approx cost
Analyst review	manual investigation	$40–$120
False escalation	unnecessary SAR	$300–$1500
Missed laundering	regulatory + reputational	$50,000–$5M

(Exact values don’t matter — ratios matter.)

We define:

C_review
C_false_escalate
C_missed_crime

Step 2 — Expected loss for each decision

For a case with probability p:

If you DECLINE

You risk missing crime.

Lossdecline=p×Cmissed_crime
Loss
decline
	​

=p×C
missed_crime
	​

If you REVIEW

You always pay analyst cost.

Lossreview=Creview
Loss
review
	​

=C
review
	​

If you ESCALATE

If innocent → wasted SAR.

Lossescalate=(1−p)×Cfalse_escalate
Loss
escalate
	​

=(1−p)×C
false_escalate
	​

